Forward Kevin Love of the Minnesota
Timberwolves will replace injured Houston Rockets center Yao
Ming on the Western Conference squad for the  National Basketball
Association â€™s All-Star game on Feb. 20.  NBA Commissioner David Stern selected Love, who will be
playing in his first All-Star game, the NBA said today in a news
release.  Yao, who was voted a starter by fans, is sidelined for the
rest of the season with a stress fracture in his left ankle.  The game will be held at the Staples Center in  Los Angeles .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
